            <div type="commentary">
                <ab>Graffito scratched on the southern face of Pier A6, looking into the Basilica’s northern corridor. The geometric decoration is reminiscent of a stylized hearth, with a series of short parallel lines crossing the entire perimeter of the shape. At present no specific interpretation is suggested.</ab>
